<paragraph id="8BC536E8D230FFA7FF49C91BB8E1FC9F" blockId="11.[146,1103,497,1203]" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">
This species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FE81C91CBAC9FDFE" box="[373,480,596,620]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FE81C91CBAC9FDFE" box="[373,480,596,620]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Sigambra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FD26C91BB877FDF9" box="[722,862,595,619]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
waters by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B19D230FFA7FC11C91BBA76FD1E" author="Shin PKS &amp; Thompson GB" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" pagination="37 - 47" refId="ref10528" refString="Shin PKS, Thompson GB. 1982. Spatial distribution of the infaunal benthos of Hong Kong. Marine Ecology Progress Series 10: 37 - 47." type="book chapter" year="1982">Shin and Thompson (1982)</bibRefCitation>
; it also has 14 pharyngeal papillae and a notopodial capillary seta on mid-body to posterior chaetigers. While having notopodial hooks starting about chaetigers 4 to 8, it is without neuropodial pectinate chaetae. These 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FC36C9FDBF66FD5F" box="[962,1103,693,717]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
specimens are comparatively small for this species: three were measured at 
<quantity id="4C829B0DD230FFA7FC1BC99DBF66FD7F" box="[1007,1103,725,749]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.28" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" unit="mm" value="3.28">3.28 mm</quantity>
for 41 chaetigers; 
<quantity id="4C829B0DD230FFA7FE95C9BDBAE8FC9F" box="[353,449,757,781]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" unit="mm" value="4.45">4.45 mm</quantity>
for 43 chaetigers; 
<quantity id="4C829B0DD230FFA7FD6CC9BDB9D1FC9F" box="[664,760,757,781]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" unit="mm" value="5.11">5.11 mm</quantity>
for 49 chaetigers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E8D230FFA7FF49C85EBAF8FB21" blockId="11.[146,1103,497,1203]" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">
It is most unlikely that all of the material attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FCBDC85FB8CFFCBD" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[841,998,791,815]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tentaculata">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FCBDC85FB8CFFCBD" box="[841,998,791,815]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. tentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is of the same species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B19D230FFA7FEDBC87FBAC6FCDD" author="Shin PKS &amp; Wu RSS &amp; Huang ZG" box="[303,495,823,847]" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" pagination="185 - 199" refId="ref10556" refString="Shin PKS, Wu RSS, Huang ZG. 2003. Marine soft-bottom infaunal communities of Hong Kong: an update. In: Shin PKS, editor. Turning the tides. A festschrift in honour of Professor Brian Morton. Hong Kong: The Marine Biological Association of Hong Kong. p. 185 - 199." type="book chapter" year="2003">Shin et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
record 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FDB3C87FB8CCFCDD" authority="(Kitamori, 1960)" baseAuthorityName="Kitamori" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[583,997,823,847]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hanaokai">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FDB3C87FB836FCDD" box="[583,799,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Sigambra hanaokai</emphasis>
(Kitamori, 1960)
</taxonomicName>
from the seabed around much of 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FE3FC81FB976FCFD" box="[459,607,855,879]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
; however, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B19D230FFA7FD18C81FBF66FCFD" author="Licher F &amp; Westheide W" box="[748,1103,855,879]" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref9604" refString="Licher F, Westheide W. 1997. Review of the genus Sigambra (Polychaeta: Hesionidae), redescription of S. bassi (Hartman, 1947), and descriptions of two new species from Thailand and China. Steenstrupia 23: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1997">Licher and Westheide (1997)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the distinction of this, amongst other, species and concluded that the characters described to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FDEAC8D0B988FC22" baseAuthorityName="Kitamori" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[542,673,920,944]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hanaokai">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FDEAC8D0B988FC22" box="[542,673,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. hanaokai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FD13C8D0B8A8FC22" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[743,897,920,944]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tentaculata">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FD13C8D0B8A8FC22" box="[743,897,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. tentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not valid, and synonymized these species. Equally, it seems untenable that the material described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FF66C891BA31FC63" baseAuthorityName="Kitamori" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[146,280,985,1009]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hanaokai">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FF66C891BA31FC63" box="[146,280,985,1009]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. hanaokai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FE97C891BAEEFC63" box="[355,455,985,1009]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, the Yellow Sea, the South 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FCFBC891B87DFC63" box="[783,852,985,1009]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">China</collectingCountry>
Sea and 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7678D230FFA7FC37C891BF2EFC63" box="[963,1031,985,1009]" name="Japan" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">Japan</collectingCountry>
is the same species as that from the northwest Atlantic (the 
<typeStatus id="54C1884AD230FFA7FD07C8B1B80AFB83" box="[755,803,1017,1041]" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FC50C8B2BF16FB80" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[932,1087,1018,1042]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tentaculata">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FC50C8B2BF16FB80" box="[932,1087,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. tentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), let alone the material from the south Atlantic, the Caribbean and the Gulf of Mexico, the Mediterranean and the Indian Ocean. Until more rigorous work, perhaps including molecular analyses, is undertaken on these taxa, it is considered that at present the material attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D6BD230FFA7FD70CF33B80DFB01" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[644,804,1147,1171]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Sigambra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="806" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tentaculata">
<emphasis id="B90EEAFAD230FFA7FD70CF33B80DFB01" box="[644,804,1147,1171]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="806">S. tentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered an aggregate of sibling species.
</paragraph>
